article.headline: Shoats has 18 in Siena's 66-53 victory against Canisius
article.description: — Justice Shoats had 18 points in Siena's 66-53 victory against Canisius on Sunday.
article.linkText: Shoats has 18 in Siena's 66-53 victory against Canisius
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. -- — Justice Shoats had 18 points in Siena's 66-53 victory against Canisius on Sunday. Shoats shot 6 of 15 from the field, including 2 for 5 from 3-point range, and went 4 for 6 from the free-throw line for the Saints (5-5, 1-1 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Brendan Coyle scored 17 points and added nine rebounds. Major Freeman had 14 points and shot 5 for 9 (2 for 6 from 3-point range) and 2 of 3 from the free-throw line. Paul McMillan IV led the Golden Griffins (0-10, 0-2) in scoring, finishing with 22 points and four assists. Jasman Sangha added 11 points and two steals for Canisius. Tana Kopa finished with six points. The Golden Griffins have lost 11 consecutive games, dating to a 72-56 defeat at the hands of Quinnipiac in the 2024 MAAC Tournament. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
